com.percussion.rx.delivery
Interface IPSDeliveryResult

public interface IPSDeliveryResult

A single delivery result describes whether a particular delivery was successful or not, and what failure occurred if one has occurred. Delivery results are generated by the delivery handlers, IPSDeliveryHandler.

Results are generated at two points in the process. The initial call to IPSDeliveryHandler.deliver(com.percussion.rx.delivery.IPSDeliveryItem) will return a delivery result. Then the call to IPSDeliveryHandler.commit(long) will return a collection of results.

The logging system will combine multiple messages from the results if needed.

Another important role of the delivery result is to carry unpublishing information from the delivery handler to be stored with the item's logging information in the database. By storing a characteristic piece of data such as path or the table and primary key, the delivered item can later be unpublished. The unpublishing information can be any serializable java data object.

getJobId

long getJobId()
Returns:
returns the delivery job id. A job id is unique to a server and form the basis of handling logs. They are used as the primary key in the status table.

getReferenceId

long getReferenceId()
Returns:
the reference id for the specific item assembling instance. These ids are unique to the database and are used as primary keys in the log table.
